Text.SourceString: I wonder what we’re doing in school tomorrow. <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> always tells us about interesting stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what we’re doing in school tomorrow. <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> always tells us about interesting stuff.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever had <NPCName>Jim’s</> smoked salmon? It’s really good!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever had <NPCName>Jim’s</> smoked salmon? It’s really good!

Text.SourceString: Sometimes he brings some when he comes over to play chess with Dad.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes he brings some when he comes over to play chess with Dad.

Text.SourceString: I have a big test tomorrow. Excuse me, <PlayerName>$player</>, but I have to get back to studying.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a big test tomorrow. Excuse me, <PlayerName>$player</>, but I have to get back to studying.

Text.SourceString: That’s what Dad told me to say when I need to work.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s what Dad told me to say when I need to work.

Text.SourceString: It’s kinda boring on the island sometimes.//I wish there was a mystery for me to solve, like in Boy Detective.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s kinda boring on the island sometimes.//I wish there was a mystery for me to solve, like in Boy Detective.

Text.SourceString: Dad says it’s not nice to wish for people to be murdered.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad says it’s not nice to wish for people to be murdered.

Text.SourceString: Do you know anything about Pokyo?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know anything about Pokyo?

Text.SourceString: Dad says we can go to the beach tomorrow since it’s a weekend. Yay!
Text.LocalizedString: Dad says we can go to the beach tomorrow since it’s a weekend. Yay!

Text.SourceString: Got any ice cream, <PlayerName>$player</>? I’m starving!
Text.LocalizedString: Got any ice cream, <PlayerName>$player</>? I’m starving!

Text.SourceString: I gotta get my homework done fast tonight. Boy Detective is coming on TV again!
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta get my homework done fast tonight. Boy Detective is coming on TV again!

Text.SourceString: I didn’t do so well on my homework last week. I don’t really get math.
Text.LocalizedString: I didn’t do so well on my homework last week. I don’t really get math.

Text.SourceString: Mom says I have to learn math if I want to be a detective, though. Guess I gotta keep working on it.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom says I have to learn math if I want to be a detective, though. Guess I gotta keep working on it.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I got to sleep in today. Getting up every morning to go to school is hard.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I got to sleep in today. Getting up every morning to go to school is hard.

Text.SourceString: If you need any coconut drinks or fish stuff, you should go to the Beach Shack!
Text.LocalizedString: If you need any coconut drinks or fish stuff, you should go to the Beach Shack!

Text.SourceString: Dad says he doesn’t need to pay for advertising with me around. But I don’t know what that means.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad says he doesn’t need to pay for advertising with me around. But I don’t know what that means.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what we’re doing in school tomorrow. <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> always tells us about interesting stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what we’re doing in school tomorrow. <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> always tells us about interesting stuff.

Text.SourceString: Dad got me this really cool kite for my birthday. It looks like a big fish.//I like to fly it in the park when it’s windy.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad got me this really cool kite for my birthday. It looks like a big fish.//I like to fly it in the park when it’s windy.

Text.SourceString: I don’t wanna go to school tomorrow. I’m tired of taking tests.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wanna go to school tomorrow. I’m tired of taking tests.

Text.SourceString: Were you really good at school, <PlayerName>$player</>? I think Dad was.
Text.LocalizedString: Were you really good at school, <PlayerName>$player</>? I think Dad was.

Text.SourceString: It’s okay if you weren’t. I’m not very good at it either.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s okay if you weren’t. I’m not very good at it either.

Text.SourceString: I’m so hungry! Is it time for dinner yet?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so hungry! Is it time for dinner yet?

Text.SourceString: Mom got me a new action figure when she went into town the other day. It’s really cool.//See? The arms go up and down, and it says a bunch of stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom got me a new action figure when she went into town the other day. It’s really cool.//See? The arms go up and down, and it says a bunch of stuff.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what Pokyo looks like. Dad says it’s a big city with lots of people and lots of noise.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what Pokyo looks like. Dad says it’s a big city with lots of people and lots of noise.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if there’s places to go fishing there.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if there’s places to go fishing there.

Text.SourceString: It’s the last day of school for this week! Yay!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the last day of school for this week! Yay!

Text.SourceString: What’s your favorite kind of ice cream? I really like mint.//It feels <Italic>windy</>in my mouth. You should try it!
Text.LocalizedString: What’s your favorite kind of ice cream? I really like mint.//It feels <Italic>windy</>in my mouth. You should try it!

Text.SourceString: Dad caught some really big fish a long time ago. He said he started fishing when he was my age.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad caught some really big fish a long time ago. He said he started fishing when he was my age.

Text.SourceString: I wish he would teach me to fish.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish he would teach me to fish.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> says even after we finish school here, we have to go to school somewhere else and get a degree. What’s that?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> says even after we finish school here, we have to go to school somewhere else and get a degree. What’s that?

Text.SourceString: I don’t wanna go to school forever.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wanna go to school forever.

Text.SourceString: I stepped on a can at the beach the other day, and it made my foot bleed.//It really hurt, but Dad put a bandage on it, and it felt better.
Text.LocalizedString: I stepped on a can at the beach the other day, and it made my foot bleed.//It really hurt, but Dad put a bandage on it, and it felt better.

Text.SourceString: There sure is a lot of garbage in the ocean. I wonder how it got there.
Text.LocalizedString: There sure is a lot of garbage in the ocean. I wonder how it got there.

Text.SourceString: It’s almost time for school exams.//I hope I’m ready.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s almost time for school exams.//I hope I’m ready.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been studying really hard, but it seems like everyone else gets it better than I do.//Guess I gotta keep working.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been studying really hard, but it seems like everyone else gets it better than I do.//Guess I gotta keep working.

Text.SourceString: I wish the ocean would warm up faster so I can go swimming. It’s still cold from Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish the ocean would warm up faster so I can go swimming. It’s still cold from Winter.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what Mom’s gonna get me for my birthday. I hope it’s the new Boy Detective shirt!
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what Mom’s gonna get me for my birthday. I hope it’s the new Boy Detective shirt!

Text.SourceString: Have you seen anything strange on the island, <PlayerName>$player</>? Any mysteries to solve?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen anything strange on the island, <PlayerName>$player</>? Any mysteries to solve?

Text.SourceString: No? Oh, okay.
Text.LocalizedString: No? Oh, okay.

Text.SourceString: Dad says all the big fish come out in Summer. I wonder where they hide during Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad says all the big fish come out in Summer. I wonder where they hide during Winter.

Text.SourceString: The Beach Shack is sooooo busy in Summer. Where do all those people come from?
Text.LocalizedString: The Beach Shack is sooooo busy in Summer. Where do all those people come from?

Text.SourceString: Do they live in the ocean and come out just to buy ice cream?
Text.LocalizedString: Do they live in the ocean and come out just to buy ice cream?

Text.SourceString: Why is it so hot? I hope Dad has some extra ice cream.
Text.LocalizedString: Why is it so hot? I hope Dad has some extra ice cream.

Text.SourceString: I don’t wanna go to school when it’s this hot. It’s too icky.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wanna go to school when it’s this hot. It’s too icky.

Text.SourceString: Dad says I should play with some kids from my class, but I don’t wanna.//<portrait=happy>I like to play alone sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad says I should play with some kids from my class, but I don’t wanna.//<portrait=happy>I like to play alone sometimes.

Text.SourceString: Dad says Fall is salmon season. I hope <NPCName>Jim</> makes some more smoked salmon!
Text.LocalizedString: Dad says Fall is salmon season. I hope <NPCName>Jim</> makes some more smoked salmon!

Text.SourceString: Hmm…was it Fall or Summer?//I can’t remember.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm…was it Fall or Summer?//I can’t remember.

Text.SourceString: It’s kinda cold out here, but the ocean is still warm. How does that work?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s kinda cold out here, but the ocean is still warm. How does that work?

Text.SourceString: Can I still go surfing?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I still go surfing?

Text.SourceString: Did you give your animals a hug today? You should make sure they’re happy.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you give your animals a hug today? You should make sure they’re happy.

Text.SourceString: It’s fun to jump in big piles of leaves.//<portrait=normal>You can make them spray everywhere, like – <Italic>woosh</>!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s fun to jump in big piles of leaves.//<portrait=normal>You can make them spray everywhere, like – <Italic>woosh</>!

Text.SourceString: Mom says farmers harvest a lot of crops in Fall. Did you harvest anything?
Text.LocalizedString: Mom says farmers harvest a lot of crops in Fall. Did you harvest anything?

Text.SourceString: Can you cook anything tasty with those veggies?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you cook anything tasty with those veggies?

Text.SourceString: No one comes to the Beach Shack when it’s cold outside.
Text.LocalizedString: No one comes to the Beach Shack when it’s cold outside.

Text.SourceString: I guess that’s because no one goes to the beach when it’s cold outside.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess that’s because no one goes to the beach when it’s cold outside.

Text.SourceString: Eating ice cream makes me feel even colder in Winter.//Brrrrr!
Text.LocalizedString: Eating ice cream makes me feel even colder in Winter.//Brrrrr!

Text.SourceString: Is it time for the Winter Market yet? Mom always buys me a new toy!
Text.LocalizedString: Is it time for the Winter Market yet? Mom always buys me a new toy!

Text.SourceString: I’m tired of wearing a jacket every day. Is it time for Summer yet?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m tired of wearing a jacket every day. Is it time for Summer yet?

Text.SourceString: I don’t like standing in the rain. It’s too wet.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like standing in the rain. It’s too wet.

Text.SourceString: I wish Mom had gotten me the Boy Detective umbrella for my birthday.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish Mom had gotten me the Boy Detective umbrella for my birthday.

Text.SourceString: Rain, rain, go away! I wanna go out and play.
Text.LocalizedString: Rain, rain, go away! I wanna go out and play.

Text.SourceString: It’s dark and wet and cold out here.//I wish I was at home.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s dark and wet and cold out here.//I wish I was at home.

Text.SourceString: Guess I can’t play outside today.
Text.LocalizedString: Guess I can’t play outside today.

Text.SourceString: That’s okay. Boy Detective is coming on TV tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s okay. Boy Detective is coming on TV tonight.

Text.SourceString: I always sleep better when it’s raining out.
Text.LocalizedString: I always sleep better when it’s raining out.

Text.SourceString: I’m getting kinda sleepy now…zzzzz…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m getting kinda sleepy now…zzzzz…

Text.SourceString: I think Dad fell asleep on the sofa again. He always does that when the TV’s on.
Text.LocalizedString: I think Dad fell asleep on the sofa again. He always does that when the TV’s on.

Text.SourceString: I hope it doesn’t rain again tomorrow. I wanna go to the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it doesn’t rain again tomorrow. I wanna go to the beach.

Text.SourceString: I don’t wanna go out when there’s thunder! It’s too scary!
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wanna go out when there’s thunder! It’s too scary!

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, I d-don’t really w-wanna t-talk right now. C-can we do it l-later?
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, I d-don’t really w-wanna t-talk right now. C-can we do it l-later?

Text.SourceString: Yikes! Thunder!
Text.LocalizedString: Yikes! Thunder!

Text.SourceString: It’s scary out here. I wanna go home!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s scary out here. I wanna go home!

Text.SourceString: The storm makes everything creepy. You can’t even see anything in the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: The storm makes everything creepy. You can’t even see anything in the rain.

Text.SourceString: Why is thunder so big and loud? It sounds like a giant foot stomping on Coral Island.
Text.LocalizedString: Why is thunder so big and loud? It sounds like a giant foot stomping on Coral Island.

Text.SourceString: I wanna go to sleep, but the thunder is keeping me awake.
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna go to sleep, but the thunder is keeping me awake.

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna be sleepy tomorrow…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna be sleepy tomorrow…

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Snow day!</>
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Snow day!</>

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll read inside while it snows.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll read inside while it snows.

Text.SourceString: You can’t really grow any plants when it’s like this, right? It would make them cold and sad.
Text.LocalizedString: You can’t really grow any plants when it’s like this, right? It would make them cold and sad.

Text.SourceString: Look at it snow out there! Is it gonna snow forever?
Text.LocalizedString: Look at it snow out there! Is it gonna snow forever?

Text.SourceString: I hope so.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope so.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what fish think of snow. Do they even know it’s there?
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what fish think of snow. Do they even know it’s there?

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Oliver</> looks busy studying.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Oliver</> looks busy studying.]

Text.SourceString: Sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>, but I gotta pay attention.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>, but I gotta pay attention.

Text.SourceString: Dad has lots of books about fishing in here. I don’t really understand most of them.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad has lots of books about fishing in here. I don’t really understand most of them.

Text.SourceString: If you catch a fish, you should show it to my dad. He knows a lot about them.
Text.LocalizedString: If you catch a fish, you should show it to my dad. He knows a lot about them.

Text.SourceString: The wind feels nice.//<portrait=annoyed>But don’t open your mouth so wide. Sand might get in it.
Text.LocalizedString: The wind feels nice.//<portrait=annoyed>But don’t open your mouth so wide. Sand might get in it.

Text.SourceString: Dad always makes a big deal out of me getting lots of fresh air. He says it’s good for kids like me.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad always makes a big deal out of me getting lots of fresh air. He says it’s good for kids like me.

Text.SourceString: What does he mean? Isn’t it good for every kid?//Like, is fresh air bad for <NPCName>Valentina</> or something?
Text.LocalizedString: What does he mean? Isn’t it good for every kid?//Like, is fresh air bad for <NPCName>Valentina</> or something?

Text.SourceString: The sky is so big! Sometimes, I just look up and stare at it.
Text.LocalizedString: The sky is so big! Sometimes, I just look up and stare at it.

Text.SourceString: I hope it doesn’t mind me staring.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it doesn’t mind me staring.

Text.SourceString: Mini golf is hard! The clubs are <Italic>really</> heavy.
Text.LocalizedString: Mini golf is hard! The clubs are <Italic>really</> heavy.

Text.SourceString: Mom said kindness is cool.//I wanna be kind so I can be cool.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom said kindness is cool.//I wanna be kind so I can be cool.

Text.SourceString: I am?! Thank you!//You’re very kind, <PlayerName>$player</>.//That makes you very cool!
Text.LocalizedString: I am?! Thank you!//You’re very kind, <PlayerName>$player</>.//That makes you very cool!

Text.SourceString: I see a lot of grown-ups going to the Tavern. I don’t know why they like it so much there.//<portrait=doubt>It’s so loud!
Text.LocalizedString: I see a lot of grown-ups going to the Tavern. I don’t know why they like it so much there.//<portrait=doubt>It’s so loud!

Text.SourceString: Dad took me to the Tavern one time to get dinner.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I’ll understand when I grow up. Who knows? I might like it then!
Text.LocalizedString: Dad took me to the Tavern one time to get dinner.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I’ll understand when I grow up. Who knows? I might like it then!

Text.SourceString: I can smell the air changing when it rains! It smells like… Errr… It smells like fish to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I can smell the air changing when it rains! It smells like… Errr… It smells like fish to me.

Text.SourceString: I can smell the air changing when it rains! It smells like… Errr… It smells like fish to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I can smell the air changing when it rains! It smells like… Errr… It smells like fish to me.

Text.SourceString: As long as I’m careful and go home before dark, I can explore the island and find bugs.
Text.LocalizedString: As long as I’m careful and go home before dark, I can explore the island and find bugs.

Text.SourceString: I know, I know. Bugs live in the wild.//<portrait=normal>We don’t take them home. My mom already taught me all that.
Text.LocalizedString: I know, I know. Bugs live in the wild.//<portrait=normal>We don’t take them home. My mom already taught me all that.

Text.SourceString: I’d rather swim than play volleyball. But nobody wants to swim with me, so I usually play volleyball instead.//The ocean is like a huge bath, and I’ll never, ever get sweaty in it.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d rather swim than play volleyball. But nobody wants to swim with me, so I usually play volleyball instead.//The ocean is like a huge bath, and I’ll never, ever get sweaty in it.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I sweat a lot when I play volleyball, and I don’t like it.//I feel all sticky. Eww…
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I sweat a lot when I play volleyball, and I don’t like it.//I feel all sticky. Eww…

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ms. Suki</> said she likes to run for fun. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ms. Suki</> said she likes to run for fun. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: Grown-ups are weird.
Text.LocalizedString: Grown-ups are weird.

Text.SourceString: I went to the lake with my class this one time, and we all collected trash.//We took it back to school and made stuff with it.
Text.LocalizedString: I went to the lake with my class this one time, and we all collected trash.//We took it back to school and made stuff with it.

Text.SourceString: We made pencil cases and trash bins!
Text.LocalizedString: We made pencil cases and trash bins!

Text.SourceString: I go to the museum with my friends sometimes.//We meet my mom there and learn things.
Text.LocalizedString: I go to the museum with my friends sometimes.//We meet my mom there and learn things.

Text.SourceString: It’s really fun. I like my mom.//She’s supersmart.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s really fun. I like my mom.//She’s supersmart.

Text.SourceString: The black marlin is my favorite fish in the world. It swims so fast, like a lightning bolt.
Text.LocalizedString: The black marlin is my favorite fish in the world. It swims so fast, like a lightning bolt.

Text.SourceString: I wish I could be as fast as a black marlin so I could catch bad guys before they do bad-guy things.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could be as fast as a black marlin so I could catch bad guys before they do bad-guy things.

Text.SourceString: The house is so boring. I wish Dad could take me fishing in the forest like <NPCName>Archie</> and his dad.//But I don’t want Dad to get too tired. He gets tired easy, and he doesn’t jump very high, so I can’t play volleyball with him either.
Text.LocalizedString: The house is so boring. I wish Dad could take me fishing in the forest like <NPCName>Archie</> and his dad.//But I don’t want Dad to get too tired. He gets tired easy, and he doesn’t jump very high, so I can’t play volleyball with him either.

Text.SourceString: There are so many kinds of sharks in the ocean! Umm… There’s mako sharks.//<portrait=normal>And then there’s blue sharks.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many kinds of sharks in the ocean! Umm… There’s mako sharks.//<portrait=normal>And then there’s blue sharks.

Text.SourceString: They’re all really fast. Maybe I can swim that fast one day.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re all really fast. Maybe I can swim that fast one day.

Text.SourceString: I like to learn about fish. Especially the really fast or really big ones! Oh, oh!//The black marlin has a really long snout, and it’s shaped like a sword!
Text.LocalizedString: I like to learn about fish. Especially the really fast or really big ones! Oh, oh!//The black marlin has a really long snout, and it’s shaped like a sword!

Text.SourceString: How cool is that? Having a sword as a nose! Whoa!
Text.LocalizedString: How cool is that? Having a sword as a nose! Whoa!

Text.SourceString: Dad made green curry for dinner last night.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad made green curry for dinner last night.

Text.SourceString: He made a lot, so I think we’ll have it again tonight.//That’s kinda sad, because it didn’t taste very good.
Text.LocalizedString: He made a lot, so I think we’ll have it again tonight.//That’s kinda sad, because it didn’t taste very good.

Text.SourceString: My mom said I have Dad’s humor and charming smile.
Text.LocalizedString: My mom said I have Dad’s humor and charming smile.

Text.SourceString: Wanna see some pictures of my fish?
Text.LocalizedString: Wanna see some pictures of my fish?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Jim</> taught me how to smoke fish a long time ago.//I think you need wood or a stone or something like that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Jim</> taught me how to smoke fish a long time ago.//I think you need wood or a stone or something like that.

Text.SourceString: No, I don’t like fishing too much. It’s fun, I guess.//<portrait=sad>But it’s also boring.
Text.LocalizedString: No, I don’t like fishing too much. It’s fun, I guess.//<portrait=sad>But it’s also boring.

Text.SourceString: Dad always tells me stories about my childhood here. And how we used to play at the beach.//<portrait=sad>But I can’t remember most of it, so… I don’t know.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad always tells me stories about my childhood here. And how we used to play at the beach.//<portrait=sad>But I can’t remember most of it, so… I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: I just feel bad for him. He seems kinda sad when he tells the stories.//I wish he could still do stuff like that now. But I know he’s kinda old, so…better not.
Text.LocalizedString: I just feel bad for him. He seems kinda sad when he tells the stories.//I wish he could still do stuff like that now. But I know he’s kinda old, so…better not.

Text.SourceString: I know I’m adopted, but I always feel like I look a bit like my mom.//<portrait=happy>Well, I look a lot more like Mom than Dad. What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: I know I’m adopted, but I always feel like I look a bit like my mom.//<portrait=happy>Well, I look a lot more like Mom than Dad. What do you think?

Text.SourceString: Dad says the Beach Shack is his favorite place in the whole world.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad says the Beach Shack is his favorite place in the whole world.

Text.SourceString: It’s kinda sandy and musty, but I like it too.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s kinda sandy and musty, but I like it too.

Text.SourceString: Seafood ramen is really good!//Have you tried it?
Text.LocalizedString: Seafood ramen is really good!//Have you tried it?

Text.SourceString: I get sad when I think about my parents. My mom and dad are kind of old.//The other day, I overheard <NpcName>Erika</> talking about <NpcName>Betty</> falling, and she had to go to the hospital.//I don’t want Dad to fall.
Text.LocalizedString: I get sad when I think about my parents. My mom and dad are kind of old.//The other day, I overheard <NpcName>Erika</> talking about <NpcName>Betty</> falling, and she had to go to the hospital.//I don’t want Dad to fall.

Text.SourceString: Have you read that cool new book? It’s called <Italic>Journal of a Weenie Kid</>.//Everyone at school is reading it.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you read that cool new book? It’s called <Italic>Journal of a Weenie Kid</>.//Everyone at school is reading it.

Text.SourceString: You know how to read, right?//<portrait=normal>I don’t want to assume, ’cause my mom said it’s rude.
Text.LocalizedString: You know how to read, right?//<portrait=normal>I don’t want to assume, ’cause my mom said it’s rude.

Text.SourceString: I can’t imagine what Dad looked like when he was a kid. I bet it was weird.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t imagine what Dad looked like when he was a kid. I bet it was weird.

Text.SourceString: I’ve seen every episode of Boy Detective a bazillion times, but watching it always makes me feel better.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve seen every episode of Boy Detective a bazillion times, but watching it always makes me feel better.

Text.SourceString: Everyone likes the detective at the end…except for the bad guys.//Who cares about them?
Text.LocalizedString: Everyone likes the detective at the end…except for the bad guys.//Who cares about them?

Text.SourceString: I wanna swim after this.//<portrait=annoyed>Oh no! I forgot my swimming trunks!
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna swim after this.//<portrait=annoyed>Oh no! I forgot my swimming trunks!

Text.SourceString: Sorry, I’m busy playing right now.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, I’m busy playing right now.

Text.SourceString: The water is kinda cool right now.//It feels nice on my feet.
Text.LocalizedString: The water is kinda cool right now.//It feels nice on my feet.
